{
  "texts": [
    "We define a capability as a fine-grained aspect of desired task behavior.",
    "That includes diverse phenomena such as linguistic (Ribeiro et al. 2020), numerical reasoning (Naik et al. 2018) and generalization (Lake and Baroni 2018) capabilities.",
    "Capabilities are often evaluated using test suites (Röttger et al. 2021; Ribeiro et al. 2020) comprising specific examples that relate to the tested capabilities.",
    "While the AI Act obliges providers of AI systems to list the capabilities of the respective system as a means of transparency, it refers to capabilities as a technical specification primarily in the context of general-purpose AI.",
    "Such AI systems are considered to represent systemic risks if they have high capabilities (see Recital 60n)."
  ]
}